fields.label: Privacy Level
fields.name: person_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this person's info?

fields.label: Person Tags
fields.name: person_tags
fields.instructions: These tags can be used as a shortcut for grouping people in your archive.	For instance Revolutionary War Patriots, Gateway Ancestors, Immigrant Ancestors, Presidential Ancestors, etc.

fields.label: Person's Generation
fields.name: person_generation
fields.instructions: The generation the person belongs to including siblings, cousins, spouses, etc.

fields.label: Article Privacy Level
fields.name: article_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this photo?

sub_fields.label: Article Page Image
sub_fields.name: article_page_image
sub_fields.instructions: Add each photo of the article separately

sub_fields.label: Article Transcription
sub_fields.name: article_transcription
sub_fields.instructions: Add an optional transcription of the image

fields.label: Article File
fields.name: article_file
fields.instructions: Upload a pdf of the image

fields.label: Article Digital Location
fields.name: article_digital_location
fields.instructions: List any places you have digital copies on backup hard drives, your computer, dropbox, etc.

fields.label: Audio Privacy Level
fields.name: audio_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this photo?

fields.label: Audio Link
fields.name: audio_link
fields.instructions: Url for anyplace online where the audio can be accessed.

fields.label: Audio Digital Location
fields.name: audio_digital_location
fields.instructions: List any places you have digital copies on backup hard drives, your computer, dropbox, etc.

fields.label: Citation Name
fields.name: citation_name
fields.instructions: This is shorthand that only you will see.	It will help when connecting citations to multiple facts or items.	For instance "Photos From Grandma" or "Letters from Historical Society"

fields.label: Given By
fields.name: citation_person
fields.instructions: Select a person from your archives who gave you this item

fields.label: Citation Source
fields.name: citation_source
fields.instructions: Select a source from your archive.

fields.label: Citation Details
fields.name: citation_details
fields.instructions: Here you can include page number, section number, paragraph number, date of publication, etc.

fields.label: Citation Facts
fields.name: citation_facts
fields.instructions: Here you can detail what facts are proven by or referenced in the citation

fields.label: Event Privacy Level
fields.name: event_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this event?

fields.label: Photo Privacy Level
fields.name: photo_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this photo?

fields.label: Photo Type
fields.name: photo_type
fields.instructions: Check as many as apply

fields.label: Add Date Range
fields.name: photo_date_range
fields.instructions: If you don't know the exact date the photo was taken you can add a range of years.

fields.label: Earliest Year
fields.name: year_earliest
fields.instructions: The earliest year the photo could possible be from

fields.label: Latest Year
fields.name: year_latest
fields.instructions: The latest year the photo could possible be from

fields.label: Photo Taken By
fields.name: photo_taken_by
fields.instructions: Connect this photo to the person in your archive who took it.

fields.label: Places In Photo
fields.name: photo_place
fields.instructions: Choose from your saved places

fields.label: Photo Digital Location
fields.name: photo_digital_location
fields.instructions: List any places you have digital copies on backup hard drives, your computer, dropbox, etc.

fields.label: Photo Album Privacy Level
fields.name: photo_album_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this photo album?

fields.label: Link to an External Album
fields.name: album_external_google
fields.instructions: Include a link to see more photos hosted on another site.	That way you don't have to upload every photo.

fields.label: Photos In Album
fields.name: album_photo
fields.instructions: Photos appear in the album in the order you select them.	New photos will be added to the end of the album.

sub_fields.label: Post External Link
sub_fields.name: post_repeater_link
sub_fields.instructions: Add a link to external sources.	This will show up as a button

fields.label: Name of Source
fields.name: source_name
fields.instructions: A source can be a person, organization, museum, website or wherever you got an item.

fields.label: Source Details
fields.name: source_details
fields.instructions: Use this field to include author, publication info or any other details about the source.

fields.label: Story Description
fields.name: story_description
fields.instructions: Briefly describe story in a few lines

fields.label: Story Privacy Level
fields.name: story_privacy
fields.instructions: Who should be able to see this story?

fields.label: External Link
fields.name: task_external_link
fields.instructions: Link to external source

fields.label: Referenced in Update
fields.name: update_referenced
fields.instructions: Select any people, places, events, stories or materials this update connected to this update.

fields.message: All registered users are able to comment on posts, materials, and other content.  In order to contribute to the archive or view private info about living people you must provide the info of a referring user.  When your referral has been confirmed you will receive an email letting you know you can start contributing.

fields.label: Contributor Request
fields.name: contributor_request
fields.message: I want to contribute to the archive
